  <span id="freeText9180509196892252314" style="display:none">To receive a free copy of any book by Charles Mahoney, please visit: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.charlesmahoneybooks.com/">http://www.charlesmahoneybooks.com/</a><br><br>Somerset Author<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1468430221i/19705658.png" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Charles Mahoney debuted in 2014 with the publication of his first novel, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20454895._Story_of_The_Ghost" title=" Story of The Ghost" rel="nofollow noopener"> Story of The Ghost</a>. Ranked high on several reader lists, it's a contemporary piece of literature in which an athletic teenage boy struggles to overcome loneliness and an escaped prisoner's lust for fame as he fields a one-player football team for a Native American school in the Sonoran Desert. His second novel is the investigative thriller <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30654530._The_Gray_Hound" title=" The Gray Hound" rel="nofollow noopener"> The Gray Hound</a>, and is currently available along with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20454895._Story_of_The_Ghost" title=" Story of The Ghost" rel="nofollow noopener"> Story of The Ghost</a> on Amazon. Forthcoming, is the mystery <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30978512._In_Defense_of_Knowing" title=" In Defense of Knowing" rel="nofollow noopener"> In Defense of Knowing</a>. It's about a dedicated youth pastor who relocates his family to a small town for his church only to find himself in a battle with an evil group of people for his young daughter’s life. Mahoney's latest work has been described as an "absolutely chilling" tale of good versus evil.<br><br><br><br><a href="http://www.charlesmahoneybooks.com" rel="nofollow noopener">Charles Mahoney</a> is on Amazon and Goodreads.</span>
